			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=367#M367">7</a> of 312
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 2594 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>I completely agree with your reasoning here. In fact, I'm seriously impressed that you would suggest this.</P>
<P>However, I would like&nbsp;to know one thing. Why do you believe this is a better solution than simply doing what SOE did for Druids and Shamans with Complete Heal? (I.e. giving reduced versions to the lesser healers) What is the exact benefit of this that makes you prefer this option?</P>
<P>There are a lot of risks associated with this path, and it would require a lot more effort on SOE's part. When comparing just warriors and knights, the effects are nearly identical. The primary difference overall is that this will allow every other class to tank much better, relatively speaking. I am not sure if this is good or bad. One of the desires of the rebalancing was that knights be given a larger gap between them and the non-tank classes. Essentially, a warrior after these changes would effectively&nbsp;reduce about 20-25% of&nbsp;a mob's damage output over a knight. That seems reasonable enough, knights have other things they can do. My real question is, what about the "light" melees? I suppose it can't be too bad if rangers are viewed as light tanks again. After all, they do have a taunt button.</P>
<DIV>On another note, I still firmly believe that warriors should have their aggro generation capabilities better spread through all levels of the class. The jump when a warrior becomes PoTime geared is too great. It really is night and day between a bazaar geared warrior and a PoTime geared warrior. The difference in aggro between a bazaar geared knight and a time geared knight is negligible. Pre-time warriors would be much more competitive with knights if their aggro was boosted in such a manner (but Time geared warriors stayed the same; this is easily accomplished by shifting aggro from gear to innate class abilities).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Couple the aggro change I've suggested with some good, useful abilities to use like you suggested (though I'm not sure your suggestions are powerful enough to offset the loss of defensive/evasive...), and I could easily see this working out.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Somewhat different tangent, and probably inappropriate for this thread, another thing SOE really should look at is scaling up knight aggro. Currently, knight aggro is locked by cast time, recast time, and raw hate values for fear/stun/snare/etc., and it NEVER goes up. If they allow this to continue unchecked, it's pretty obvious what the end result in a couple expansions will be. Namely, knights will be completely obsolete in aggro generation and suffering from the exact same problems that warriors were in PoP. Fortunately, it's not a big deal yet and SOE has plenty of time to notice this and hopefully correct it. Knight aggro at the PoTime and GoD level seems fine enough, all they need to do is scale it up from there.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Anyway, here's to hoping we can finally come up with some reasonable ideas that all three tank classes can agree on, for once.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							65 Shadowknight<br>Machin Shin<br>Xegony
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
