<img src="/eq/i/icons/Classes/shadowknight.gif" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=375#M375">8</a> of 312
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 2564 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV><FONT face=Verdana size=2>The following is copy/pasted from one of Slein's threads at SK.org:</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Verdana size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Verdana size=2>Defensive is generally viewed to be a huge overpowering factor in favor of warriors, and the reason the tank classes are so far out of balance. It's been suggested a few times, by knights and some of the more balance-minded warriors alike, that the best path toward tank class balance is to remove defensive/evasive from the game entirely, and give the warriors a larger innate mitigation to compensate. <BR><BR>It is only overpowered, however, because only one of the three tank classes has access to it. If knights and warriors both had access to defensive and a melee immunity disc from day one, the current class balance problems would not have arisen (a few minor spell/skill tweaks would likely have been sufficient). If all three classes that are intended to be able to tank had defensive, all three would be able to tank and we would not have the abhorrent imbalance in tanking ability we see to day. <BR><BR>Ignoring knights' current conundrum, defensive serves a useful purpose. It makes the difference between tanks (warriors - exclude knights for the moment) and non-tanks quite clear on the big mobs, such that only the tanks can stand up to the "boss" mobs. It also means that trash mobs don't have to be able to completely destroy non-tanks in order to not be entirely trivial to the tanks, as one can't be defensive all the time - it's reserved for the big fights. <BR><BR>By giving knights a defensive discipline, the above would indeed be true for ALL of the tank classes. Knights would be closer to warriors in tanking than non-tanks are to knights (the inverse is currently true). <BR><BR>Also noteworthy is that over the past several expansions (prior to GoD) it had been established that warriors were generally ideal for the boss mobs, while knights were the preferred add tanks. Removing defensive would make this harder to re-establish. Warriors' mitigation superiority would then be in effect ALL the time. It would mean that trash mobs' dificulty would take that superiority into account. With warriors now having gained so much ground on the traditional knight aggro superiority, this would do little to return knights to their off-tanking role, unless they received defensive improvements to put them level with warriors, and that clearly will not happen. <BR><BR>By leaving defensive/evasive in the game, and adding similar disciplines for knights, the disciplines can be tailored to the traditional roles of the classes. <BR><BR>See </FONT><FONT face=Verdana color=#cccccc size=2>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=shadowknightbalance&amp;message.id=1436</FONT><FONT face=Verdana size=2> for what I believe to be the ideal knight disciplines to achieve this. This would be preferable to both giving knights a carbon-copy of warrior defensive and to removing defensive entirely. It would leave warriors as the best tanks for boss mobs, return knights to being the best off-tanks, and create the needed tanking desparity between tanks and non-tanks on the mobs that matter, without making trash mobs excessively hazardous. <BR><BR>Furthermore, defensive is one of the few factors contributing to tanks "stacking" on raids. With no defensive, there'd be no reason to switch tanks, and thus there would only be a need for one tank on anything that doesn't stand to 1-round the MT. This would be bad for warriors in the long run, as it would reduce the number of warriors needed for the MT spot. If, in order to counter this, mobs were tuned such that the chance of 1-rounding warriors was a real concern virtually all the time on boss mobs, it would create the problem of "1-rounder spikes" chewing through all of the raids warriors due to bad luck with the RNG. <BR><BR>From a non-balance standpoint, removing defensive/evasive, and the ensuing re-balancing of content that would necessarily go with it would be a lot more work for the devs than would implementing the discs I proposed in the linked thread. The difference in terms of effort to implement would be staggering. <BR><BR>As with anything balance related, copy/paste it anywhere you feel so inclined, just leave a link here so we can follow the ensuing discussion.</FONT></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Krushum Gudended<br>Dread Lord of Formidable<br>Innoruuk Server
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
