			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=6758'>







<img src="/eq/i/icons/Classes/warrior.gif" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=387#M387">11</a> of 312
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 2478 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>Here, specifically, is the reason why I Feel deensive and evasive should be removed from the game instead of giving knights a lesser form of defensive.</P>
<P>Defensive is game breaking because it is too powerful. When new encounters are designed, they are designed to be challenging <EM>for defensive</EM>. They are not tuned to be challenging for a non disced tank for warrior, they are tuned so they they will KILL a non defensive warrior.</P>
<P>At this point, the warrior tanking the mob, knows that pretty much the reason why he can do it, is because of one single discipline more than anything else. He can't really attribute it to him being geared up well enough, he's using defensive as the crutch to survive. to put it bluntly, it's DEFENSIVE saving the day, not the TANK. When the disc becomes more important than the tank, it's a balance issue.</P>
<P>Removing defensive from the game would reduce some of the completely stupid numbers we're seeing for melee in the game as it is. Take Quarm, doing what, quad for 3800 or 3900, it's not the tank that you need for the mob, it's the DISC you need for the mob. The requirement of "having" to have the disc is becomeing way too overexaggerated. Remove defensive and upgrade warrior damage taking abilities slightly&nbsp;(rough numbers being 12.%% warrior increased total mitigation plus avoidance plus&nbsp;25-30% reduction in&nbsp;named damage)&nbsp;and you only need Quarm hitting for 2500-3000, and it's even *slightly* more difficult than before. Tanks are still going to die and you'll definitely still need a MTO, as overall you'll have a slightly higher warrior chance of dying, BUT it won't be so clearly "you're fairly sure you're gonna live while the disc is up, but as soon as that disc timer runs out, kiss your ass goodbye".</P>
<P>The incredible inflation in named mob damage that needs to be designed into the game to challenge an overpowered ability, would be reduced,&nbsp;damage wouldn't go up so high, so fast. IMO it would prolong the success of the game.</P>
<P>As a side effect of damage output reduction, healing would gain a side benefit in that it wouldn't be so important, and marginalized&nbsp;and made useless so quickly. It's more useful to be able to heal yourself for 1k when the mob only hits for 2k instead of 3k, for example. Healing requirements to keep a tank alive wouldn't go up so sharply after defensive wears off.</P>
<P>Additionally, I feel that knights are fine the way they are, with minor improvements to their spells and abilities.&nbsp;They do NOT need a major upgrade like mini defensive. They need the content tuned instead. Coincidentally, my proposal for removing defensive from the game would also require content tuning. Boom, two birds with one stone.</P>
<P>I don't know about you folk, but it ticks me off that I owe my survival in a fight to one all-important disc, than my abilties and gear level as the premiere tank in the game.</P>
<DIV></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
