			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=6758'>







<img src="/eq/i/icons/Classes/warrior.gif" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=388#M388">12</a> of 312
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 2472 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>I'd like to take issue with one misperception, that with this idea, there'd be "no need" to have any tankswitches on raids.</P>
<P>I don't know about you, but I see PLENTY of tank switches even when a warrior is under defensive. The healing is a bit off, the mob gets some lucky max hits, and the disc'd warrior goes splat.</P>
<P>Given the fact that defensive is a discipline that reduces spike damage due to the level of mitigation involved, defensive warriors have less spiky damage than a non defensive warrior. A non defensive warrior, logically, then, will be taking a it more spike damage. Mobs will be getting lucky rounds a bit more often, tanks are going to die, switches are going to need to happen.</P>
<P>Add on top of the fact that mobs&nbsp;would then &nbsp;be doing, on an average basis, slightly more damage to the warrior, this would be to make it balanced. The warrior will NOT be taking the much greater damage as soon as the disc wears off, but he willbe taking a bit more damage throughout the fight to compensate. This is to keep the challenge in the game.</P>
<P>Additionally, all further content would be designed with the LACK of defensive in mind, so further expansions would be designed to challenge their tanking abilities, and not challenge the ridiculously overpowered defensive. </P>
<P>Defensive scales in how much damage it&nbsp;gets rid of, the harder mobs hit. To take a very simplistic (and not quite correct) approach to illustrate, with defensive in the game, you want the warrior to take X damage, you gotta make the mob do twice as much. You want the warrior to take 5000 a hit, you're going to be seeing the mob put out 10000 damage, A ridiculous number in my opinion. You want the warrior to take 5000 a hit with no defensive in the game, you make the mob hit for 5000. Nods to the fact that defensive only affects DI damage, yes, I know, but I simplified to give an example.</P>
<P>Removing defensive and rebalancing names doesn't JUST help the plates... it betters the game as a whole.</P>
<DIV></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
