			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=390#M390">13</a> of 312
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 2459 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>Let's make some comparisons here. Knights vs warriors; the way it is now, the way it would be with knights getting a form of defensive and knights with defensive removed from the game. Call it against a hard hitting, high DI mob, max hit... 4k double. At this point, the raid is out of warriors.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>The way it is now:</P>
<P>Knight sees no warriors left alive. The rest of the raid grimaces as the knight attempts to tank the defensive tuned mob. Odds are, wave goodbye to that knight, he just can't take the beating. Warrior is taking about 55-60% less damage than the knight (45% defensive, 15% innate better tanking, BUT the DI change is rendered as I understand it, less useful</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Knights get mini defensive (30%)</P>
<P>Knight&nbsp;steps up to the plate. Warrior taking 60% less damage than pre-disc knight, 45% less damage than post-disc knight. (30% disc covers 15% warrior damage taking plus an extra 15%.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Defensive removed from the game:</P>
<P>Knight steps up to the plate. Knight taking 27.5% more damage than the warrior (15% pre-fix difference, plus 7.5% bonus to warrior mitigation and 5% bonus to avoidance to replace defensive.</P>
<P>As you can see, my solution actually does more to being the plate classes into line with warriors than does the hybrid defensive idea. The actualyl difference will be less, taking into account stuns, heals, and lifetaps. Stuns in XP groups will make a difference, not on nameds, however.</P>
<P>I'd like to also state that with this fix, adding maybe a 5% bonus to mitigation (the -1DI for knights, -2DI for warriors) might be a good idea as well, to further differentiate the hybrid plates from the chain and leather classes, the tanking difference is proabably a little low.</P>
<P>Thoughts?</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
