		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>Yes, and no, Grud.</P>
<P>the reason why it's more than the 45% that defensive gives, is defensive gives a further inrease iver the 15% tanking advantage that warriors already have. Now on average, that 15% is pretty solid.</P>
<P>Defensive, of course, doesn't give exactly 45% more mitigation. It changes based on the DB-DI of the mob. high DB, you'll want evasive instead. You'll notice that I used a high DI mob in that example to keep the number fairly close to what I stated.</P>
<P>Your actual mileage may very, but it should be pretty close in that example, and the actual damage taken will change, BUT the relationship of how well the knight will tank the mob compared to the warrior should remain very nearly the same.</P>
<P>So yeah, it's not exact, even though I used an example to minimize the disparity between theoretical and actual numbers seen.</P>
