<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=406#M406">24</a> of 312
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 2385 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Fanboi, why do you feel the knight disc ideas are overboard? The currently suggested ones (short duration, short refresh) really can't possibly affect the warrior class in its&nbsp;main role, but will help a lot with offtanking.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And, I suppose the main thing that concerns me about removing defensive/evasive is the thought that raid adds that quad for 1.5k+ aren't going to be tuned down at all, most likely, which means that knights are still going to get gibbed on them and warriors are still going to tank significantly better on them than knights, due to ever-present damage reduction. And while your changes would drastically help knights on raid boss MTing, knights do not really want or need to be able to tank raid bosses drastically better. All they want is to be able to do it in a pinch briefly, if say a mob is at 10% and the last warrior goes down, a knight being able to step up to take it down from there would be nice. But, with your changes, a knight tanking from 100% to 0% would be quite viable on cutting edge content. Shrug, though. I'm sure it could work out somehow.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>What I want to see is something that ensures knights keep being the best at their offtanking role, just like warriors keep being the best at their main tanking role. I suppose you could always go a different direction and make knights the absolute gods of aggro, capable of pulling a mob off anyone with even low hp aggro in one, quick cast. But, er... that would be pretty screwed up, in a lot of ways.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							65 Shadowknight<br>Machin Shin<br>Xegony
							</div>
								
