	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=14316'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<span style='color:#3399FF;font-weight:bold; '>Chania</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Champion<br>
			
				Posts: 340<br>
				
				Registered: 03-26-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=14316'>







<img src="/eq/i/icons/Classes/shadowknight.gif" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=408#M408">25</a> of 312
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 2375 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>You can't take defensive out of the game at this stage. It is not even desirable as Slein has pointed out, it would make tank switches unecessary and further dumb down the game. It is much easier and more balancing to the game as a whole for the ability to be spread out amongst the 3 tanking classes, it would&nbsp;put them a cut above the rest of the classes for tanking, which is a good thing.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>But you have to realize that if this change went live, of the 3 tanking classes, Warriors would be dead last for desireability for normal groups. If tanking is adequate for the 3 classes, then you can remove that from the desirability equation. If you remove that, what else do Warriors offer vs Knights? Not a whole lot. Some will say that is as it should be, Warriors will have the raid roles all locked up due to thier small, but in raids, important tanking advantage. The thing is, raids is not all EQ is. I don't think Warriors would be happy with just a raid role and no group desireability. So the question is a complicated and thorny one.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>In conclusion, Warrior one-sidedness makes it difficult for them to share their core ability with other classes. Either Warriors get more group friendly abilities like Warcries and the like, or I don't see Knights getting a long lasting damage mitgation disc.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27539">Chania Thanatos</a><br><a href="http://www.echoesineternity.org">Echoes in Eterntity</a><br><a href="http://strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/Chania/fullsize/ChaniaTheme.mp3">"Fear now, Snare later" </a>
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
